RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 5 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $16,000 And Since Th en Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.)For Two Year Olds under International Medication Protocol. Horses entered to compete shall not be eligible to receive furosemide less than twenty-four (24) hours prior to post time for the race. (If deemedi nadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUEEN AIKO hopped up leaving the gate, bumping with the horse to her outside in the process, saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader under a hold up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn, and dueled to the wire, drifting out and brushing mildly with EASTER SUNDAY GIRL in midstretch but holding the win. EASTER SUNDAY GIRL bumped with the horse to her inside leaving the gate, raced in the three path early, stalked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path, began a challenge passing the quarter pole and dueled to the finish, brushing lightly with QUEEN AIKO in midstretch and giving way late. PLATINUM DIVA raced in the two path around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, came around the far bend still in the two path, raced in tight quarters headed into the stretch and chased the top two home from there. HIPATIA bumped with the horse to her outside at the start, raced off the pace in the three path through the opening half mile, began a bid from the three path coming around the far bend and improved position from there. TOURIST STYLE saved ground around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, began to move up from the four path coming around the far turn and improved position further in the lane while never truly threatening. SUPER SNEAKY was fractious in the gate, bumped soundly with the horse to her inside at the break, raced in the four path early, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and faded in the lane. DIAMOND ROMANCE saved ground around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path and was empty in the stretch. THE RIDER OF HORSE EIGHT, PLATINUM DIVA, CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST HORSE TEN, EASTER SUNDAY GIRL, CITING INTERFERENCE AT THE QUARTER POLE. A SEPARATE CLAIM OF FOUL WAS MADE BY HORSE TEN, EASTER SUNDAY GIRL, AGAINST HORSE FIVE, QUEEN AIKO, CITING INTERFERENCE IN MIDSTRETCH. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.
